Introduction {#intro}
===============

Issue: please don’t rely on this document yet as it’s still under discussion and development. 

This document describes the [generic data model](https://netwerk-digitaal-erfgoed.github.io/cm-implementation-guidelines/#generic-data-model)
for publishing linked data.
It is designed as a Schema.org application profile.

Classes {#classes}
===============

Publishers *MUST* type each published resource as one or more of the following classes: 

- schema:CreativeWork
- schema:Event
- schema:ImageObject / schema:VideoObject / schema:MediaObject
- schema:Organization
- schema:Person
- schema:Place

Publishers *MAY* use more fine-grained classes alongside these top-level classes.

<div class="example">
    A photograph is typed as both top-level schema:CreativeWork and the more specific schema:Photograph:

    <pre highlight=json-ld>
        {
          "@context": "https://schema.org/",
          "@id": "https://example.com/dataset1/resource1"
          "@type": ["CreativeWork", "Photograph"]
        }
    </pre>
</div>

